<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25538</anchor> <rss>anon.149.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.149</addr>  <route>anon.149.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>We must show that each <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">proposition</link>; in fact, each <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> is <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">contractible</link> as <link href="erct-002N.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002N" title="Biinvertible maps are contractible">biinvertible maps are contractible</link>, and <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">contractible types are propositions</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25539</anchor> <rss>erct-002W.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002W</addr>  <route>erct-002W.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">embeddings</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002W.agda" type="external">erct-002W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is an <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">embedding</link>.</p>
 
   
   
 
</mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25540</anchor> <rss>erct-002N.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002N</addr>  <route>erct-002N.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002N.agda" type="external">erct-002N.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">biinvertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25541</anchor> <rss>anon.158.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.158</addr>  <route>anon.158.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>As <link href="erct-002D.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002D" title="From biinverses to quasi-inverses">biinvertible maps are quasi-invertible</link> and <link href="erct-002M.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002M" title="Quasi-invertible maps are contractible">quasi-invertible maps are contractible</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25542</anchor> <rss>erct-001K.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001K</addr>  <route>erct-001K.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">Contractible</link> types are <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">propositions</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001K.agda" type="external">erct-001K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link>, then it is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25543</anchor> <rss>anon.180.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.180</addr>  <route>anon.180.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>As <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible</link> with some centre <tex>a:A</tex>, we have for any <tex>x,y:A</tex> identifications <tex>\chi _x  \colon  a = x</tex> and <tex>\chi _y \colon  a = y</tex>. Therefore, we identify <tex>x</tex> with <tex>y</tex> using <tex>\chi _x ^{-1}   \cdot   \chi _y</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25544</anchor> <rss>erct-001H.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001H</addr>  <route>erct-001H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Contractibility</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001H.agda" type="external">erct-001H.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be <em><strong>contractible with centre <tex>a:A</tex></strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex> is equipped with an identification <tex>\chi _x \colon  a = x</tex>. We say that <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong>contractible</strong></em> when it comes equipped with some <tex>a:A</tex> such that <tex>A</tex> is contractible with centre <tex>a</tex>. We sometimes refer to a contractible type as a <em><strong>singleton</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25545</anchor> <rss>erct-001Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001Q</addr>  <route>erct-001Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Fiber</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001Q.agda" type="external">erct-001Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The <em><strong>fiber</strong></em> of a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> at an element <tex>b:B</tex> is the type consisting of elements <tex>a \colon  A</tex> equipped with identifications <tex>p \colon  fa=b</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25546</anchor> <rss>erct-001I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001I</addr>  <route>erct-001I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Propositions</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001I.agda" type="external">erct-001I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be a <em><strong>proposition</strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex>, the type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractibility">contractible with centre</link> <tex>x</tex>, i.e. all elements of <tex>A</tex> are identified.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>